text: The 2020 United States presidential election in Indiana was held on Tuesday, November 3, 2020, as part of the 2020 United States presidential election. Incumbent President Donald Trump, and running mate Vice President Mike Pence had won 11 electoral votes in the Electoral College. == References == Category:2020 United States presidential election Category:2020s in Indiana
title: 2020 United States presidential election in Indiana
